Day 34 — Stochastic & Mini-Batch Gradient Descent

📌 Overview

On Day 34, I learned Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) and Mini-Batch Gradient Descent, two improved versions of Batch Gradient Descent used to train models more efficiently.

🧠 Types of Gradient Descent

1️⃣ Batch Gradient Descent

Uses entire dataset

Stable but slow for large datasets


2️⃣ Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)

Uses one data point at a time

Faster but more noisy updates


3️⃣ Mini-Batch Gradient Descent

Uses small batch of data

Balanced approach (fast + stable)
